description: From dis- +‎ range. Compare Old French desrengier, French déranger. See derange, disrank.

verbs.description: disrange (third-person singular simple present disranges, present participle disranging, simple past and past participle disranged)

examples: how cautious we should be not to disturb that delicate connexion and thread of circumstances , which are seldom disranged , even by the smallest alteration
